Whoops!  I missed Rule 815 which specifies to send stuff directly to officers.
I'll take care of that momentarily... However, since I'm not officially 
registered yet, does that count against me?  Anyway, "Vanyel" is a character
in a series of novels.

Also, I would like to Proto:

PROTO-PROPOSAL DB2 (Vanyel)
(Creates a rule)
Combination of Related Rules

  When more than four rules exist which are related to the same topic, any 
Player may put forth a Non-Rule-Change Proposal requesting these rules to
be Combined.  This proposal must be voted on, and will have an Adoption Index
of 1.  If that Proposal is passed, the Player who first Proposed to Combine
the Rules will be appointed to the temporary position of Combiner of Rules
X, Y, ..., Z (where "X, Y, ..., Z" is the list of rules to be combined).  This
position will have a one-time salary of five Points.  The new Combiner of Rules
X, Y, ..., Z shall then proceed as soon as possible to combine all the Rules
he is charged to combine.  In the resulting Proposal, all conceivable 
situations should be resolvable exactly as they would were Rules X, Y, ..., Z
still in effect.  The Type of this Proposal shall be (Combines Rules).  Once
completed, this Proposal will be sent to the Speaker as with standard Rule-
Change Proposals.  This Proposal shall have an Adoption Index of 3.  If
passed, the resulting rule will be Mutable, unless the Mutation laws have
been passed, in which case it will have a Mutation Index of 1.

  Since there is no actual change made to the Adjudication of Rules, this
would be a Legal Rule and is *not* in conflict with any of 109, 110, 111,
or 115.  This rule supersedes all other rules regarding Combination of 
Rules.
**End of Proto-proposal**

Vanyel



